    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Once the LES protocol is out we expect to run Mist with the light client enabled, but until then, hang on!\n\nAs for the other issue, when you run geth **after** Mist is running it will tell you that a node is already running (and there's no reason to run another one). However if, for some reason, you'd like to run a second instance you'll have to specify a different `datadir` and `port` (e.g. `geth --datadir /tmp/datadir1 --port 30304`).\n\nWhen you run mist **after** running `geth` mist will auto connect to the already running node. \n",
